**Case Study:  Online Identity Theft using Phishing Attack**

In 2023, a college student named Rohan fell victim to an online identity theft scam that started with what had seemed like a normal email from his bank. Like many students, he relied heavily on online banking and didn’t think twice before opening the message. The email warned him about “suspicious activity” and asked him to verify his account through using a link.

Trusting the message he saw, Rohan clicked the link and entered his login details on a website that looked almost identical to his bank’s official page. What he didn’t realize was that it was a fake site created to steal his important information. Within a few hours, the attacker used his credentials to access his account to carry out unauthorized transactions.

Cases like this often target people who are busy, distracted, or unaware of how this works. Scammers usually create a sense of urgency so that victims act quickly without verifying the source.

The impact on Rohan was stressful and time consuming. He lost money, had to deal with bank to recover his account, and spent weeks fixing the damage that had occured. It also made him more cautious about his online habits afterwards.

This situation shows how a small mistake online can lead to a serious consequences, and why it’s important to double check links and never share sensitive information carelessly.
